                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/3662.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Chihuahua</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Chihuahua</hi>
                        </placeName>.<lb/>[<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-19">undated</date>] (Received April
                        19, 1912—3.30 p.m.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Two Americans have been imprisoned here since March 16 by the military
                    authorities without any excuse whatever; the detention has just come to my
                    notice. One of them is an honorably discharged sailor of our Navy. Have demanded
                    their immediate release.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
